1. git init : Initialize empty git repository.
2. git status : Gives the status.
3. git add file-name.extension : to add a file in repository. e.g.: git add hello.txt
4. git commit -m "comments" : to commit file which we just added
5. git add '*.extension' : add files using wildcard. e.g.: git add '*.txt' - will add all text files.
6. git commit -m 'comments' : commit all files
7. git log : to see all logs, changes we made so far.
8. git remote add origin https://github.com/url/repo-name.git : to add our local repo to git server
9. 
